05:22.314 --> 05:24.357
- Up a little bit.

05:24.358 --> 05:25.775
A little more.

05:30.698 --> 05:32.031
All the way up.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.158
Come on, guys.

05:38.205 --> 05:40.583
- Oh, look, Santa's reindeer.

05:41.709 --> 05:44.669
Now Dasher, now Dancer, now Prancer…

05:44.670 --> 05:46.638
- There's a car.

05:48.090 --> 05:50.174
- Now Dasher, now Dancer, now…

05:50.175 --> 05:52.760
- Get out of the street.

05:52.761 --> 05:54.137
- Now Dasher!

05:54.138 --> 05:55.430
Now Dancer!

05:55.431 --> 05:57.015
Now…

05:57.016 --> 05:58.141
- Watch it!

06:02.521 --> 06:03.317
- Prancer!

06:10.571 --> 06:11.743
- I've been telling
the council for years

06:11.744 --> 06:13.284
these decorations are too old.

06:13.285 --> 06:16.911
- Almost went right
through that man's windshield.

06:16.912 --> 06:18.161
- Oh, look.

06:18.162 --> 06:19.129
- Looks like Santa's

06:19.130 --> 06:22.000
only going to have seven
reindeer this year.

06:25.294 --> 06:26.796
- Up and out, people.

06:26.797 --> 06:28.212
Let's clear the streets.

06:28.213 --> 06:29.089
Don't want any accidents.

06:29.090 --> 06:30.966
Let's clear the street.

06:33.802 --> 06:36.271
- Aren't you going to fix him?

06:37.639 --> 06:40.183
Aren't you going to fix him?

06:40.184 --> 06:41.401
- I don't know.

06:42.519 --> 06:43.644
- They've got to fix him.

06:43.645 --> 06:45.730
Santa needs all his reindeer.

06:45.731 --> 06:48.775
Maybe he can't fly without Prancer.

06:48.776 --> 06:51.486
- It's not the real Prancer.

06:51.487 --> 06:53.154
It's just wood.

06:53.155 --> 06:54.281
- I know that.

06:56.075 --> 06:57.292
It's just wood.

07:03.290 --> 07:05.380
- I don't know, you
got a lot of hours on it.

07:05.381 --> 07:08.380
- Hey, that tractor's
only three years old.

07:08.381 --> 07:10.505
- Yeah, but I can
only give you 1,900 for it.

07:10.506 --> 07:11.676
- It's worth twice that.

07:11.677 --> 07:13.596
- Look, I know you're
having a rough time here.

07:13.597 --> 07:15.843
- Dad, guess what?

07:15.844 --> 07:16.640
- 3,000.

07:17.554 --> 07:18.599
- A reindeer fell

07:18.600 --> 07:21.015
and almost went right
through a man's windshield.

07:21.016 --> 07:21.812
- Not now!

07:23.102 --> 07:24.604
- That's my best offer.

07:24.605 --> 07:26.230
Take it or leave it.

07:32.694 --> 07:33.570
- Leave it.

07:35.155 --> 07:36.406
What are you dressed up for?

07:36.407 --> 07:40.287
- It was the Christmas
pageant today, remember?

07:41.286 --> 07:42.328
- Yeah.

07:42.329 --> 07:43.579
How'd it go?

07:43.580 --> 07:45.164
- Good.

07:45.165 --> 07:46.582
- That's good.

07:46.583 --> 07:47.583
- You know what?

07:47.584 --> 07:50.884
Shawn Griswold was supposed
to carry the baby Jesus,

07:50.885 --> 07:52.463
but he lost it.

07:52.464 --> 07:54.799
They had to wrap up a bunch of rags

07:54.800 --> 07:56.518
and use that instead.

08:05.894 --> 08:07.271
Dad, are we poor?

08:09.523 --> 08:10.775
- No, we're not poor.

08:10.776 --> 08:13.072
We're just down on our luck.

08:14.111 --> 08:16.864
- Well, will we be up on our luck?

08:18.407 --> 08:21.576
- I'm doing everything I can.

08:21.577 --> 08:24.287
- I could help if you let me.

08:24.288 --> 08:26.586
- You're just a little girl.

08:27.541 --> 08:29.292
- Are we going to starve?

08:29.293 --> 08:30.920
- No, of course not.

08:32.754 --> 08:34.927
Stop worrying about
these things, will you?

08:34.928 --> 08:37.799
We're going to be all right.

08:37.801 --> 08:38.927
Apples.

08:40.511 --> 08:42.058
We're going to eat apple sauce

08:42.059 --> 08:45.349
and apple cider and apple pie.

08:45.350 --> 08:50.313
And then stewed apples and
baked apples and dried apples.

08:50.314 --> 08:51.361
Apple butter.

08:52.941 --> 08:53.783
Heck, no.

08:53.784 --> 08:55.151
We're not gonna starve.

09:00.741 --> 09:02.118
- Hi, Aunt Sarah.

09:06.538 --> 09:08.789
Steve, can you fix my sled?

09:08.790 --> 09:10.458
- No.

09:10.459 --> 09:11.299
' No?

09:11.300 --> 09:12.089
- No.

