<i>♫ We wish you a merry Christmas ♫</i>

09:40.322 --> 09:42.448
<i>♫ And a happy new year ♫</i>

09:42.449 --> 09:44.122
<i>♫ Now bring us some figgy pudding ♫</i>

09:44.123 --> 09:45.576
- Dinner!

09:45.577 --> 09:46.577
' Coming!

09:46.578 --> 09:48.167
<i>♫ Now bring us some figgy pudding ♫</i>

09:48.168 --> 09:50.084
<i>♫ And bring some right here ♫</i>

09:50.085 --> 09:51.921
<i>♫ We won't go until we get some ♫</i>

09:51.922 --> 09:53.543
<i>♫ We won't go till we get some ♫</i>

09:53.544 --> 09:55.211
- Ah, wish.

09:55.212 --> 09:56.054
Wish.

09:56.055 --> 09:57.423
Flop, flop, wish.

09:59.091 --> 10:01.389
There's going to be a
full moon this Christmas.

10:01.390 --> 10:04.184
- Don't talk with your mouth full.

10:06.723 --> 10:07.519
- Sorry.

10:10.894 --> 10:13.818
That means there's bound to
be magic things happening.

10:13.819 --> 10:15.189
- Give me a break.

10:15.190 --> 10:17.275
- You don't know anything about it.

10:17.276 --> 10:18.198
Our teacher…

10:18.199 --> 10:20.236
- There is something about a full moon.

10:20.237 --> 10:21.737
Nancy Hooper works over at the hospital

10:21.738 --> 10:23.411
and she says whenever there's a full moon,

10:23.412 --> 10:24.954
the patients on the eighth floor,

10:24.955 --> 10:27.159
you know, the mental patients,

10:27.160 --> 10:29.996
they all start acting up like crazy.

10:29.997 --> 10:30.837
- Really?

10:30.838 --> 10:31.671
- Mm hmm.

10:31.672 --> 10:32.507
' How?

10:32.508 --> 10:35.503
- Why don't you go there on
Christmas Eve and find out?

10:35.504 --> 10:37.169
They'll show you magic.

10:37.170 --> 10:39.047
- Why are you so nasty?

10:40.882 --> 10:41.849
- You want to eat like an animal,

10:41.850 --> 10:44.391
take your food out to the barn.

11:45.113 --> 11:47.615
- It's not an easy
thing that we're playing here.

11:47.616 --> 11:49.492
- It's not easy on me either.

11:49.493 --> 11:51.746
You think I like not being
able to provide for her?

11:51.747 --> 11:52.792
- You do provide.

11:52.793 --> 11:54.330
- No, I don't.

11:54.331 --> 11:57.380
I can't even get a bank loan anymore.

12:00.796 --> 12:04.173
- Have you told her yet, John?

12:04.174 --> 12:05.508
You've got to.

12:05.509 --> 12:06.351
- I know.

12:07.636 --> 12:08.432
I know.

12:13.600 --> 12:15.568
- I still don't see why
she's been coming over

12:15.569 --> 12:17.019
so much lately.

12:17.020 --> 12:18.190
- She's your aunt.

12:18.191 --> 12:19.814
She's trying to help out.

12:19.815 --> 12:22.942
- She asked dad if he told me yet.

12:22.943 --> 12:24.026
Told me what?

12:24.027 --> 12:25.700
- Maybe they're gonna get married.

12:25.701 --> 12:27.154
- Don't be revolting.

12:27.155 --> 12:29.281
She's married to my uncle Arnold.

12:29.282 --> 12:30.329
- Maybe they were talking

12:30.330 --> 12:33.579
about a surprise, a Christmas
present they got you.

12:33.580 --> 12:36.706
- You know Santa's the one
who brings all the presents.

12:36.707 --> 12:37.998
- Oh, right.

12:37.999 --> 12:39.625
Santa Claus.

12:39.626 --> 12:40.751
- You know it's true.

12:40.752 --> 12:43.963
My mother told me, and she'd never lie.

12:43.964 --> 12:47.550
- Let's not talk about it
anymore right now, though.

12:47.551 --> 12:50.930
There's some serious sledding to be done.

12:51.847 --> 12:53.514
- We're the first ones.

12:53.515 --> 12:56.815
- The only ones crazy enough to do this.

13:23.378 --> 13:25.087
- Hey, you!

13:25.088 --> 13:27.006
This is private property.

13:27.007 --> 13:28.634
Get off my property.

13:30.218 --> 13:31.927
- Steer away!

13:31.928 --> 13:33.012
Turn!

13:33.013 --> 13:34.477
- I'm trying, I'm trying-

13:34.478 --> 13:36.771
- Don't you come here, you hooligans!

13:38.977 --> 13:40.853
Go away, you violators.

13:41.777 --> 13:43.900
You hit me and you'll go to juvenile hall.

13:45.776 --> 13:46.698
Oh.

13:47.527 --> 13:49.111
Oh, my floribundas.

13:49.112 --> 13:50.362
Oh.

13:50.363 --> 13:51.363
You animals!

13:51.364 --> 13:53.583
Oh, oh, oh, my floribundas.

13:54.659 --> 13:55.993
You rascals!

13:55.994 --> 13:58.078
Oh, I'll get even with you.

13:58.079 --> 13:58.955
I'll catch you.

13:58.956 --> 14:00.539
I'll catch you, you.

14:09.883 --> 14:11.931
I'll get YOU, YOU, YOU…

14:13.345 --> 14:15.097
Terrorists!

14:16.681 --> 14:18.149
- Would she recognize us?

14:18.150 --> 14:19.643
- I don't think so.

14:26.316 --> 14:27.483
See you tomorrow.

14:27.484 --> 14:28.451
_ Okay, bye-

16:28.480 --> 16:31.029
- I've never seen one like you.

16:41.206 --> 16:43.124
You're not afraid of me.

17:24.243 --> 17:26.787
Dad, I just saw a deer in the woods.

17:26.788 --> 17:27.630
- Come in here.

17:27.631 --> 17:29.248
- It was interesting.

17:29.249 --> 17:30.749
It was so big.

17:30.750 --> 17:32.668
It looked like a giant.

17:32.669 --> 17:36.046
It was so weird, you would never imagine.

17:36.047 --> 17:37.390
- How many times have I told you

17:37.391 --> 17:38.882
not to go near McFarland's?

17:38.883 --> 17:39.848
- Dad, will you listen…

17:39.849 --> 17:40.810
- She just gave me a call

17:40.811 --> 17:42.723
and says you ruined some
of her flower bushes.

17:42.724 --> 17:44.598
You wanna guess who's gonna pay for those?

17:44.599 --> 17:45.639
- But, dad!

17:45.640 --> 17:48.189
- I want you to
stay away from there.

17:48.190 --> 17:52.312
- It looked just like the one in my room.

17:52.313 --> 17:53.109
Hey!

17:54.065 --> 17:55.691
- You hear me?

17:55.692 --> 17:57.945
- Yeah, I do, clad.

18:29.517 --> 18:31.894
- I believe you saw a deer in the woods.

18:31.895 --> 18:33.854
There's lots of 'em around.

18:33.855 --> 18:35.823
But I don't believe it was Santa's,

18:35.824 --> 18:37.816
and I don't believe it flies.

18:37.817 --> 18:39.990
- It looks just like this one, Prancer.

18:39.991 --> 18:42.865
See the white mark on his forehead?

18:43.907 --> 18:44.783
Hey, wait a minute.

18:44.784 --> 18:47.411
Remember it was Prancer that
fell down on Main Street?

18:47.412 --> 18:49.203
- That's right, it was.

18:49.204 --> 18:50.871
- So is this one.

18:50.872 --> 18:54.541
I have a magazine that had
all the reindeers lined up.

18:54.542 --> 18:56.418
I cut them out and this is the order.

18:56.419 --> 18:58.629
This is Prancer and this is,

18:58.630 --> 19:00.598
this is Prancer, Dancer,

19:01.549 --> 19:03.300
okay, Dasher, Dancer, Prancer,

19:03.301 --> 19:05.677
this is Vixen and this is Prancer.

19:05.678 --> 19:08.430
- Are you going to eat your pickle?

19:08.431 --> 19:11.058
- The moon's almost full!

19:11.059 --> 19:13.435
It'll be full on Christmas Eve.

19:13.436 --> 19:14.278
Don't you see?

19:14.279 --> 19:15.613
It all fits together.

19:15.614 --> 19:18.273
- The problem is, Jessie,

19:18.274 --> 19:21.026
I don't believe in Santa Claus anymore.

19:21.027 --> 19:22.569
- What?

19:22.570 --> 19:24.034
- I mean, think about it.

19:24.035 --> 19:26.078
How could one man climb
down all the chimneys

19:26.079 --> 19:28.242
in the world in one night?

19:28.243 --> 19:30.041
- He's magical, Carol.

19:31.287 --> 19:33.247
- It doesn't make sense.

19:33.248 --> 19:36.969
- Well, Carol, not everything
in the world can be explained.

19:36.970 --> 19:39.211
- I've never seen Santa Claus,

19:39.212 --> 19:41.755
and I've clone a lot of looking.

19:41.756 --> 19:43.382
- You've never seen God, either.

19:43.383 --> 19:45.134
Does that mean there's no God?

19:45.135 --> 19:48.720
- Well, how do we know
about that for sure?

19:48.721 --> 19:52.933
- Because if there's no
God, there's no heaven.

19:52.934 --> 19:55.602
- Well, maybe there isn't.

19:55.603 --> 19:57.947
- All right for you, Carol Wetherby.

19:57.948 --> 20:00.317
You're not my friend anymore.

20:01.901 --> 20:04.236
- What did I say?

20:04.237 --> 20:06.947
- That there was no heaven!

20:06.948 --> 20:07.744
' $0?

20:08.867 --> 20:11.165
- What about my mother then?

20:18.585 --> 20:20.169
- I said I'm sorry.

20:20.170 --> 20:22.337
Jessie, come on!

20:22.338 --> 20:23.383
I was just kidding.

20:23.384 --> 20:25.132
I believe in Santa Claus, okay?

20:25.133 --> 20:27.097
I believe in God, and I believe in heaven.

20:27.098 --> 20:29.136
- Do you believe it was Prancer?

20:29.137 --> 20:29.979
- Yes.

20:29.980 --> 20:31.769
- I don't believe you.

20:36.477 --> 20:37.524
- There's my mom.

20:37.525 --> 20:40.399
She's taking me Christmas shopping.

20:41.691 --> 20:43.159
Talk to you later.

22:23.751 --> 22:24.877
- Get in here!

22:27.171 --> 22:27.967
Come on!

22:36.014 --> 22:40.017
I talk and I talk and you
just don't listen, do you?

22:40.018 --> 22:43.061
What are you doing out there by yourself?

22:43.062 --> 22:44.479
- Looking for the reindeer.

22:44.480 --> 22:46.106
- I've told you never to go into the woods

22:46.107 --> 22:48.108
by yourself this time of year.

22:48.109 --> 22:50.077
A hunter will shoot you!

22:57.493 --> 22:59.536
- Where were you going, daddy?

22:59.537 --> 23:01.747
- Just groceries.

23:01.748 --> 23:05.218
You know, looking at some feed and things.

23:07.045 --> 23:11.048
- I heard you and Aunt Sarah
talking the other night.

23:11.049 --> 23:13.268
What does told me yet mean?

23:14.844 --> 23:15.640
- What?

23:15.641 --> 23:18.014
- What does told me yet mean?

23:20.350 --> 23:21.226
- Oh, baby.

23:23.019 --> 23:24.271
You know, it's just not right

23:24.272 --> 23:28.400
when a little girl's got to
grow up without a mom around.

23:33.363 --> 23:36.829
We've been talking about maybe
you going to live with her.

23:36.830 --> 23:39.543
- No, daddy, please,
I don't wanna do that.

23:39.544 --> 23:41.082
- I know you don't.

23:41.954 --> 23:43.580
This is a hard thing for me to do,

23:43.581 --> 23:46.002
but I got to think about
what's best for you.

23:46.003 --> 23:47.798
- You're what's best for me.

23:47.799 --> 23:49.294
- No, I'm not.

23:49.295 --> 23:51.639
I can't buy you the things you want.

23:51.640 --> 23:54.633
Can't give you an education.

23:54.634 --> 23:57.729
Sarah will be able to do those things.

23:59.138 --> 24:00.390
- Please, daddy.

24:02.100 --> 24:03.266
Please.

24:03.267 --> 24:05.235
I want to stay with you.

24:07.397 --> 24:09.695
Daddy, I know we argue, but,

24:12.860 --> 24:14.820
please, daddy, please.

24:14.821 --> 24:17.916
- Honey, us arguing hasn't
got anything to do with it.

24:17.917 --> 24:22.244
It's just not right that I'm
away from the house so much.

24:22.245 --> 24:25.044
- Send Steve if someone has to go.

24:26.332 --> 24:27.916
- He's older than you.

24:27.917 --> 24:29.501
I need his help.

24:29.502 --> 24:30.628
- I help, too.

24:31.504 --> 24:33.302
- I know you do.
- I can do everything he does.

24:33.303 --> 24:34.467
He'll get too old for work.

24:34.468 --> 24:35.637
I can take his place.

24:35.638 --> 24:38.135
Please, daddy, please.

24:38.136 --> 24:39.928
- You'll only be 30 miles away.

24:39.929 --> 24:40.771
- 30 miles!

24:40.772 --> 24:42.853
That's like a billion, two trillion,

24:42.854 --> 24:43.941
a thousand miles…

24:43.942 --> 24:45.642
- Calm down, will ya?

24:45.643 --> 24:47.519
Families do this for
each other all the time.

24:47.520 --> 24:49.648
They help each other out
when things get tough

24:49.649 --> 24:52.607
and things are tough for me right now.

24:52.608 --> 24:55.152
- I'm gonna run away if she comes for me.

24:55.153 --> 24:56.496
- I don't wanna
hear you talk like that.

24:56.497 --> 24:59.453
- I will if she comes
and you'll never find me.

24:59.454 --> 25:00.574
- Stop it, Jessica!

25:00.575 --> 25:01.783
- Dad, look out!

25:12.670 --> 25:13.920
It's him!

25:13.921 --> 25:15.969
- Wait, stay here!

25:19.844 --> 25:21.344
- He's hurt, daddy.

25:21.345 --> 25:23.063
- Stay away from him.

25:31.814 --> 25:33.441
- We gotta help him.

25:49.207 --> 25:50.582
Daddy, no!

25:50.583 --> 25:51.550
- It's hurt.

25:53.461 --> 25:55.462
It's been wounded, Jessie.

25:55.463 --> 25:56.305
- No!

25:56.306 --> 25:57.594
- Let go!

25:58.925 --> 25:59.765
- You can't!

25:59.766 --> 26:00.679
It's the one I saw!

26:00.680 --> 26:01.518
It's Santa's!

26:01.519 --> 26:05.013
- Jessie, he's just gonna suffer.

26:06.307 --> 26:07.307
- No, no!

26:07.308 --> 26:08.685
I hate you, I hate you!

26:08.686 --> 26:11.478
- All right, you hate me, you hate me!

26:34.794 --> 26:37.593
- I'm going to look over this way.

26:38.923 --> 26:40.882
- Don't even think about it.

26:51.060 --> 26:52.607
This is gonna stop.

29:10.950 --> 29:12.076
- You're here.

29:13.911 --> 29:16.380
How did you know where I live?

29:22.962 --> 29:24.838
Do you want me to help you?

29:25.932 --> 29:27.300
I won't hurt you.

29:33.556 --> 29:34.773
Are you hungry?

29:53.534 --> 29:55.577
I gotta get you out of here.

29:55.578 --> 29:58.377
Dad will shoot you if he sees you.

30:28.652 --> 30:31.531
Everything's going to be all right.

30:35.201 --> 30:36.576
It's okay.

30:40.331 --> 30:41.127
Come on.

30:43.334 --> 30:44.130
Come on!

30:49.381 --> 30:52.430
I know what will get you out of here.

30:56.430 --> 30:57.226
Come on.

30:59.350 --> 31:01.318
It's a Christmas cookie.

31:21.121 --> 31:21.917
Come on.

31:23.040 --> 31:25.625
Come on, you can do it.

32:00.452 --> 32:01.248
Come on.

32:03.831 --> 32:04.627
Come on.

32:06.876 --> 32:07.672
Come on.

32:12.381 --> 32:13.507
You can do it.

32:20.389 --> 32:22.107
That's it, that's it.

32:23.225 --> 32:24.601
Come on, over here.

32:43.495 --> 32:44.291
Come on.

32:46.874 --> 32:51.004
I'll get more cookies but
you gotta come in here first.

32:53.339 --> 32:55.592
That's it, come on, come on.

33:29.750 --> 33:31.127
You gotta let me.

33:38.342 --> 33:42.438
I'll get more help, but you
got to stay here till then.

34:01.907 --> 34:04.659
- Come on, we're going to miss our bus.

34:04.660 --> 34:05.456
- Coming.

34:14.335 --> 34:16.304
- You forgot the dishes
last night, Jessica.

34:16.304 --> 34:17.342
- Sorry, dad.

34:20.384 --> 34:23.344
- Something's been
eating our little trees.

34:23.344 --> 34:24.312
- Which?

34:24.313 --> 34:27.556
- The little chestnuts.

34:27.558 --> 34:29.141
- What do you think it was?

34:29.143 --> 34:29.983
- Oh, I don't know.

34:29.984 --> 34:31.024
From the looks of the droppings

34:31.025 --> 34:33.819
I'd say it might have been a deer.

34:34.898 --> 34:37.190
- Must have been hungry
if it was eating wood.

34:37.192 --> 34:38.034
- Wood.

34:38.034 --> 34:39.404
That's what they eat.

34:39.405 --> 34:42.612
If I see 'em do it,
they'll be eating lead.

34:42.614 --> 34:43.831
- See you, dad.

35:06.847 --> 35:08.723
- Forgot my homework.

35:08.724 --> 35:09.644
- Too late now.

35:09.645 --> 35:10.483
- 1 got to.

35:10.484 --> 35:12.268
- Then you'll have to walk.

35:12.269 --> 35:13.145
- Go ahead!

35:14.646 --> 35:15.897
See ya later!

35:15.898 --> 35:18.617
- Not if I see you first!

35:44.676 --> 35:46.974
- This isn't a very healthy breakfast,

35:46.975 --> 35:50.431
but it'll have to do until
I can get you some hay.

35:50.432 --> 35:53.151
And you did eat our little trees.

35:56.146 --> 35:59.857
Oh, Prancer, you're
getting worse and worse.

35:59.858 --> 36:01.826
I'm going for some help.

36:10.077 --> 36:11.285
- You okay?

36:11.286 --> 36:12.082
- Benton!

36:14.206 --> 36:15.332
Doctor Benton!

36:17.584 --> 36:18.506
Doctor Benton!

36:18.507 --> 36:20.425
- Whatever it is can wait til tomorrow.

36:20.426 --> 36:22.046
I've been up all night.

36:22.047 --> 36:22.969
- Can't wait!

36:22.970 --> 36:24.090
Emergency!!

36:25.634 --> 36:26.430
Please?

36:27.511 --> 36:28.979
Just come, please.

36:35.853 --> 36:39.027
I brought someone to help you, Prancer.

36:40.774 --> 36:43.493
- Oh, my God, if it's a reindeer.

36:51.201 --> 36:53.786
You tricked me into this.

36:53.787 --> 36:55.163
- Uh-uh.

36:55.164 --> 36:56.757
I said there's an animal
that needs your help

36:56.758 --> 36:58.666
and that's the truth.

36:58.667 --> 37:00.214
I think he's dying.

37:07.634 --> 37:09.760
Where are you going?

37:09.761 --> 37:10.601
- I'm sorry.

37:10.602 --> 37:11.392
I can't.

37:12.472 --> 37:13.314
- You're a doctor.

37:13.315 --> 37:15.183
You're supposed to help animals.

37:15.184 --> 37:16.184
- Domestic animals.

37:16.185 --> 37:17.768
I thought it was a cow.

37:17.769 --> 37:19.191
- But he'll die!

37:19.192 --> 37:20.855
- Talk to mother nature.

37:20.856 --> 37:23.735
- Doctor Benton, this
is very, very important.

37:26.653 --> 37:28.030
You have no idea!

37:34.786 --> 37:36.162
No!

37:36.163 --> 37:36.959
He'll die!

37:39.583 --> 37:41.167
- Let go of my truck.

37:41.168 --> 37:43.294
- He's one of Santa's.

37:43.295 --> 37:45.630
Prancer, actually.

37:45.631 --> 37:48.341
- I'm so glad to hear that.

37:48.342 --> 37:49.182
- It is!

37:49.183 --> 37:50.553
- Would you please stop?
- It's Prancer.

37:50.554 --> 37:51.928
If you don't help,

37:51.929 --> 37:54.305
he'll never make it
back home by Christmas.

37:54.306 --> 37:55.146
- Would you please stop doing that?

37:55.147 --> 37:56.435
- Maybe there won't…
- Your dad's going…

37:56.436 --> 37:57.400
- Even be a Christmas…
- To hear about this.

37:57.401 --> 37:59.143
- If he doesn't get back.

38:05.025 --> 38:09.362
- Young lady, I was up half
the night with a pregnant cow

38:09.363 --> 38:11.239
and a crazy horse.

38:11.240 --> 38:13.288
I'm tired, my hand hurts,

38:14.534 --> 38:16.624
I've got a sick wife to tend to.

38:16.625 --> 38:18.338
I can't help you.
- But I'm telling you.

38:18.339 --> 38:20.331
He's one of Santa's!

38:20.332 --> 38:21.800
- Then call Santa!

38:22.918 --> 38:24.636
And let go of my car.

38:29.258 --> 38:31.636
- Probably couldn't help him anyways.

38:31.637 --> 38:33.512
Doctors are just liars.

38:34.554 --> 38:37.306
They never make anyone better!

38:47.317 --> 38:48.693
Is he going to be okay?

38:48.694 --> 38:50.111
- Too soon to tell.

38:50.112 --> 38:52.280
Should take a while to heal.

38:52.281 --> 38:53.783
Hold his head away from me.

38:53.784 --> 38:55.658
- I really don't think this is necessary.

38:55.659 --> 38:58.828
He's probably used to being around people.

38:58.829 --> 39:00.454
- What am I, an elf?

39:00.455 --> 39:01.789
Hold his head down.

39:01.790 --> 39:04.417
And keep that on after I leave, you hear?

39:04.418 --> 39:05.214
They bite.

39:10.882 --> 39:15.886
- Isn't he the most beautiful
thing you've ever seen?

39:15.887 --> 39:18.015
- Like a cow with antlers.

39:23.812 --> 39:27.398
Don't know what a reindeer
is doing this far south.

39:27.399 --> 39:29.948
Must have escaped from that Christmas show

39:29.949 --> 39:32.236
over at Riverdales.

39:32.237 --> 39:33.409
I'll give 'em a call.

39:33.410 --> 39:34.488
' No!

39:34.489 --> 39:36.741
Please, I don't want anybody to know.

39:36.742 --> 39:37.664
Especially daddy.

39:37.665 --> 39:39.502
I don't think he'd understand.

39:39.503 --> 39:42.163
- I gotta give 'em a call just in case.

39:42.164 --> 39:43.541
But I'll make you a deal.

39:43.542 --> 39:47.636
I'll give you a couple days
to tell your father yourself.

39:49.504 --> 39:50.300
- Deal.

39:54.593 --> 39:57.303
History's going to love you for this.

39:57.304 --> 39:58.851
- Oh, go to school.

40:00.766 --> 40:01.562
- School!

40:03.310 --> 40:04.150
- I swear I don't know

40:04.151 --> 40:05.487
what you're thinking about half the time.

40:05.488 --> 40:07.857
Your head's always off
in the clouds somewhere!

40:07.858 --> 40:10.316
You don't just show up for
school when you feel like it!

40:10.317 --> 40:11.737
- It's almost vacation, anyway,

40:11.738 --> 40:13.863
and all I missed was finger
painting and I didn't see…

40:13.864 --> 40:15.701
- That's the very thing I'm talking about!

40:15.702 --> 40:17.493
The very thing I'm worried about!

40:17.494 --> 40:19.289
I've gotta go off to Benton Harbor tonight

40:19.290 --> 40:22.370
and who knows what you're gonna get up to.

40:22.371 --> 40:24.874
You going to tell me why you were late?

40:24.875 --> 40:26.832
Are you listening to me?

40:26.833 --> 40:27.629
- No.

40:29.294 --> 40:30.134
- You're not?

40:30.135 --> 40:31.675
- No, I mean, I'm not going to tell you

40:31.676 --> 40:33.799
why I was late for school.

40:35.133 --> 40:36.258
- Fine.

40:36.259 --> 40:37.636
Have it your way.

40:43.892 --> 40:44.768
- Hello.

40:44.769 --> 40:45.894
Mister Benton?

40:47.437 --> 40:49.235
This is Jessica Riggs.

40:50.273 --> 40:51.113
- Yes.

40:51.114 --> 40:51.902
What?

40:51.903 --> 40:52.776
Huh?

40:52.777 --> 40:54.073
- Jessica Riggs.

40:57.447 --> 41:00.041
I was wondering if you
called the Christmas show.

41:00.042 --> 41:02.701
- Yes, it's not theirs.

41:02.702 --> 41:04.495
- Thanks, sir.

41:04.496 --> 41:05.292
I knew it.

41:07.999 --> 41:09.750
- Darnedest thing.

41:09.751 --> 41:12.220
Where did that deer come from?

41:13.130 --> 41:15.297
- I have to babysit my crazy sister.

41:15.298 --> 41:16.924
Of course I've got her locked in her room,

41:16.925 --> 41:20.896
so I probably could just
sneak out of the house.

41:22.431 --> 41:24.978
She's on a mission to find some reindeer.

41:24.979 --> 41:27.103
My dad almost made a
road pizza out of him,

41:27.104 --> 41:29.230
but she thinks he can fly.

41:31.440 --> 41:33.818
No, not my dad, the reindeer.

41:55.213 --> 41:56.260
- Suppertime.

42:01.678 --> 42:04.477
This is the part I told you about.

42:06.516 --> 42:09.268
You tear apart the baby's rattle,

42:09.269 --> 42:12.396
see what makes noise inside.

42:12.397 --> 42:15.441
But there's a veil
covering the unseen world

42:15.442 --> 42:19.163
which not the strongest
man could tear apart.

42:20.071 --> 42:21.288
No Santa Claus?

42:23.783 --> 42:27.913
Thank God he lives and lives
forever 1,000 years from now.

42:29.414 --> 42:31.963
10 times 10,000 years from now.

42:34.377 --> 42:38.507
He'll continue to make glad
the heart of childhood.

42:41.718 --> 42:44.929
I can't read as good as my mom did.

42:44.930 --> 42:48.230
But you understand what it means, right?

42:50.894 --> 42:55.024
I bet Santa doesn't think
you'll get back in time.

42:56.274 --> 42:58.072
I better let him know.

43:01.947 --> 43:03.574
I love you, Prancer.

43:05.742 --> 43:06.538
But!

43:07.911 --> 43:08.911
What about me?

43:08.912 --> 43:10.129
Do you love me?

43:24.219 --> 43:25.427
Say cheese!

43:46.533 --> 43:47.950
- Did you get that?

43:47.951 --> 43:49.994
- Ho ho ho, little buddy.

43:49.995 --> 43:51.370
Of course I did.

43:51.371 --> 43:53.920
Let's see, Skeletor, slime pit,

43:56.751 --> 43:58.879
skateboard, and handcuffs.

44:00.630 --> 44:01.672
- Right.

44:01.673 --> 44:03.048
- Ho ho ho.

44:03.049 --> 44:04.346
Merry Christmas.

44:06.886 --> 44:07.728
Whoa!

44:07.729 --> 44:10.190
You're getting kind of
heavy for Santa's lap,

44:10.191 --> 44:12.058
aren't you little girl?

44:12.976 --> 44:13.816
- I'm sorry.

44:13.817 --> 44:14.935
I don't have any time for chitchat.

44:14.936 --> 44:16.937
I know you're not the real Santa.

44:16.938 --> 44:18.147
- Whoa.

44:18.148 --> 44:19.231
Of course I am.

44:19.232 --> 44:21.572
- But can you get this letter to him?

44:21.573 --> 44:23.946
- Why don't you just put a stamp on it

44:23.947 --> 44:25.490
and drop it in the mailbox?

44:25.491 --> 44:26.697
- It's too late for that.

44:26.698 --> 44:27.698
Please believe me.

44:27.699 --> 44:30.828
This is a matter of utmost importance.

44:32.287 --> 44:35.581
Prancer's in the shed near my house!

44:35.582 --> 44:37.425
I plan to take him to Antler Ridge

44:37.426 --> 44:39.636
on December 23rd, midnight.

44:42.130 --> 44:44.673
- All that's in the letter?

44:44.674 --> 44:45.969
- Here's a picture of him.

44:45.970 --> 44:49.014
That way Santa will know
you're telling the truth.

44:49.015 --> 44:50.888
- Do you think he'd doubt me?

44:50.889 --> 44:51.731
- Admit it.

44:51.732 --> 44:53.599
You're not the real Santa.

44:53.600 --> 44:55.059
- Okay, okay-

44:55.060 --> 44:56.518
Keep it to yourself.

44:56.519 --> 44:57.987
- Can you help me?

45:01.274 --> 45:05.027
- I'll do everything I possibly can.

45:05.028 --> 45:05.870
- Thanks.

45:05.871 --> 45:07.830
- Oh, wait a minute now.

45:08.990 --> 45:11.784
Is that all you want for Christmas?

45:11.785 --> 45:14.495
- Well, for now, anyways.

45:14.496 --> 45:16.715
I really don't want to live with my aunt,

45:16.716 --> 45:20.836
but I don't know if Santa
can do anything about that.

45:22.962 --> 45:25.681
- Can we hurry it
along a little bit, Santa?

45:25.682 --> 45:27.221
- Yes, sir.

45:30.095 --> 45:30.935
- Go on, honey.

45:30.936 --> 45:31.771
It's your turn.

45:31.772 --> 45:33.231
Go on up there, quick.

45:33.232 --> 45:34.473
There you go.

45:34.474 --> 45:35.270
- On!

45:36.935 --> 45:38.352
Well.

45:38.353 --> 45:40.321
And what do you want for Christmas,

45:40.322 --> 45:42.648
you little devil, you?

45:42.649 --> 45:45.243
- Put the Minot robbery on three,

45:45.244 --> 45:48.284
the farmers on welfare story on five.

45:51.116 --> 45:54.034
- I got something to cheer you up, pal.

45:54.035 --> 45:57.665
This will be perfect
for tomorrow's edition.

46:05.922 --> 46:08.298
- You've got to swear, Carol.

46:08.299 --> 46:09.676
- I said I would.

46:10.552 --> 46:12.395
- Cross your heart, swear not to tell.

46:12.396 --> 46:13.554
If you do, I'll…

46:13.555 --> 46:14.351
- I swear!

46:18.143 --> 46:19.309
- Ready?

46:19.310 --> 46:20.186
- I'm ready.

46:20.186 --> 46:20.982
I'm ready!

46:26.241 --> 46:27.110
Oh, my God!

46:29.028 --> 46:30.487
- It's Prancer.

46:30.488 --> 46:31.364
Go ahead.

46:31.365 --> 46:32.489
Pet him.

46:32.490 --> 46:33.330
- No.

46:33.331 --> 46:34.246
It's okay.

46:34.247 --> 46:36.288
I don't like animals that much, anyway.

46:36.289 --> 46:38.334
- Come on, that's not an animal.

46:38.335 --> 46:41.039
- What are you doing here?

46:41.040 --> 46:42.082
- It's a bird.

46:42.083 --> 46:42.923
It's a plane.

46:42.924 --> 46:43.759
It's a hat rack.

46:43.760 --> 46:45.836
- It's a reindeer, you nerd.

46:48.673 --> 46:52.217
- Looks like enough
meat to last the winter.

46:53.720 --> 46:54.762
Whoa!

46:54.763 --> 46:55.804
Hurt me.

46:55.805 --> 46:57.306
My knees are shaking.

46:57.307 --> 46:59.480
- If you tell clad, I'll
never speak to you again.

46:59.481 --> 47:01.185
- Is that a promise?

47:01.186 --> 47:02.186
Dad!

47:02.187 --> 47:03.270
Oh, dad!

47:03.271 --> 47:04.111
Hey, dad!

47:04.112 --> 47:05.106
Guess…

47:05.107 --> 47:06.356
- Shut up, Steve.

47:06.357 --> 47:07.199
- Shut up?

47:07.200 --> 47:08.525
- Look, I'll make you a deal.

47:08.526 --> 47:10.654
You don't tell dad and I'll
clean out the barn for you

47:10.655 --> 47:12.324
until the end of the year.

47:12.325 --> 47:14.290
- You're lousy at cleaning the barn.

47:14.291 --> 47:16.205
- Name your price, then.

47:17.243 --> 47:18.039
- Hm.

47:19.954 --> 47:23.254
I don't wanna wash any dishes till June.

47:26.711 --> 47:27.507
- Deal.

47:28.546 --> 47:30.088
- By the way,

47:30.089 --> 47:33.342
I wouldn't take any more feed
from the barn if I were you.

47:33.343 --> 47:36.386
- Now look,
Steve, he has to eat.

47:36.387 --> 47:38.727
- Well then you guys can buy some oats.

47:38.728 --> 47:39.807
- With what?

47:39.808 --> 47:40.648
- I don't know.

47:40.649 --> 47:42.144
- You wanna give us some money?

47:42.145 --> 47:43.941
- We don't have any money.
- You know,

47:43.942 --> 47:47.105
dad's noticed the missing hay.

47:47.106 --> 47:50.651
He thinks it's the deer getting in.

47:50.652 --> 47:51.617
He says he's going to…

47:51.618 --> 47:53.362
- Don't say the word.
- Be waiting with his gun.

47:55.657 --> 47:57.032
See you, Prancer.

47:57.033 --> 47:57.909
Bye, Carol.

47:59.536 --> 48:01.332
- I only need two more days.

48:01.333 --> 48:02.918
Then I'll take him up to Antler Ridge

48:02.919 --> 48:04.873
and Santa will come and get him.

48:04.874 --> 48:05.714
- He will?

48:05.715 --> 48:06.834
- Yeah, I sent him a letter.

48:06.835 --> 48:07.802
It's all worked out.

48:07.803 --> 48:11.338
- Kid isn't playing with a full deck.

48:11.339 --> 48:12.548
- Listen, Steve.

48:12.549 --> 48:15.259
Nobody, and I mean nobody but us three,

48:15.260 --> 48:16.762
can know about Prancer.

48:16.763 --> 48:18.303
- Don't worry.

48:18.304 --> 48:22.275
I wouldn't want anybody
to find out you're nuts.

48:25.562 --> 48:26.984
- No, Prancer, I have no cookies.

48:26.985 --> 48:31.110
If you didn't eat so fast,
you'd still have some hay left.

48:32.068 --> 48:34.491
Where am I going to
get the money for oats?

48:34.492 --> 48:37.114
They cost something like $15 a bag.

48:37.115 --> 48:38.907
- Don't look at me.

48:38.908 --> 48:40.831
I spent all mine on Christmas presents.

48:40.832 --> 48:42.494
- Maybe we can earn it.

48:42.495 --> 48:43.620
We're on vacation.

48:43.621 --> 48:44.918
We can get jobs.

48:45.790 --> 48:47.541
Don't worry, Prancer.

48:47.542 --> 48:49.419
I won't let you starve.

48:50.628 --> 48:51.424
