01:13:37.405 --> 01:13:38.873
Aren't you, fella?

01:13:52.003 --> 01:13:53.962
Nobody answer that.

01:13:53.963 --> 01:13:55.681
I'm tired of having to
explain to everybody

01:13:55.682 --> 01:13:57.721
why I sold that reindeer.

01:14:00.053 --> 01:14:03.097
- May I be excused, please?

01:14:03.098 --> 01:14:04.315
- Yes, you may.

01:14:11.189 --> 01:14:15.192
- Sorry about the mess
he made in the house.

01:14:15.193 --> 01:14:18.788
I'll do the dishes after
everyone's through.

01:15:14.335 --> 01:15:15.755
- Where do you think you're going?

01:15:15.756 --> 01:15:17.217
- None of your beeswax.

01:15:17.218 --> 01:15:19.341
- You're heading for town
at night in a snowstorm

01:15:19.342 --> 01:15:21.383
and it's none of my business?

01:15:21.384 --> 01:15:23.102
You're gonna try and spring Prancer.

01:15:23.103 --> 01:15:24.511
- So what if I am?

01:15:24.512 --> 01:15:25.354
- I just wondered

01:15:25.355 --> 01:15:29.317
why do you need a sack
full of clothes to do it.

01:15:30.310 --> 01:15:34.188
Come on, Jessie, what are the clothes for?

01:15:34.189 --> 01:15:35.031
You're gonna tell me what you're doing

01:15:35.032 --> 01:15:36.991
or I'm gonna go get dad.

01:15:38.234 --> 01:15:40.068
- I'm not coming back.

01:15:40.069 --> 01:15:41.528
- Boy, that's just great.

01:15:41.529 --> 01:15:42.496
Come on, Jessie.

01:15:42.497 --> 01:15:44.031
Come back to the house.

01:15:44.032 --> 01:15:45.949
Come on, don't be crazy.

01:15:45.950 --> 01:15:49.745
HEY, are you going to make me drag you?

01:15:49.746 --> 01:15:50.793
- Go ahead, drag me.

01:15:50.794 --> 01:15:53.758
I'll just find another way to leave.

01:15:54.667 --> 01:15:56.793
- Am I the only sane
one left in this family?

01:15:56.794 --> 01:15:57.841
- Look, Steve, I'm not going

01:15:57.842 --> 01:16:00.839
to ever, ever live with Aunt Sarah.

01:16:00.840 --> 01:16:01.924
- Aunt Sarah?

01:16:01.925 --> 01:16:03.095
- Dad wants to send me there

01:16:03.096 --> 01:16:05.093
and I really don't want to go.

01:16:05.094 --> 01:16:06.428
- He does?

01:16:06.429 --> 01:16:09.056
Why is everyone keeping me
in the dark about everything?

01:16:09.057 --> 01:16:10.477
- I didn't think you'd care.

01:16:10.478 --> 01:16:11.315
- Of course I do.

01:16:11.316 --> 01:16:12.809
- I thought
maybe you might be glad.

01:16:12.810 --> 01:16:13.652
- Of course not.

01:16:13.653 --> 01:16:14.737
Now come on back, Jess.

01:16:14.738 --> 01:16:16.730
We'll work this out.

01:16:16.731 --> 01:16:18.449
- Dad doesn't want me.

01:16:18.450 --> 01:16:19.983
- Sure, he does.

01:16:19.984 --> 01:16:21.780
- He doesn't treat me right.

01:16:21.781 --> 01:16:23.699
- He's just mixed up right now.

01:16:23.700 --> 01:16:26.198
- He doesn't love me,
doesn't understand me.

01:16:26.199 --> 01:16:28.951
- Maybe he doesn't
understand you all the time.

01:16:28.952 --> 01:16:29.874
I don't either.

01:16:29.875 --> 01:16:32.748
That doesn't mean I don't love you.

01:16:35.708 --> 01:16:36.630
Come on, come on home.

01:16:36.631 --> 01:16:38.048
I'm tired of talking about this.

01:16:38.049 --> 01:16:39.962
- I can't, Steve.

01:16:39.963 --> 01:16:44.093
With Prancer gone, there's
nothing left for me in this town.

01:16:52.600 --> 01:16:53.476
Bye, Steve.

01:17:33.308 --> 01:17:36.602
- Figured you might need
some help with the jailbreak.

01:17:36.603 --> 01:17:37.570
Don't think I'm gonna try

01:17:37.571 --> 01:17:39.690
and talk you out of running away anymore.

01:17:39.691 --> 01:17:43.609
Whatever you wanna do is fine with me.

01:17:43.610 --> 01:17:44.907
- Thanks, Steve.

01:18:03.755 --> 01:18:05.464
- We gotta hurry.

01:18:05.465 --> 01:18:07.092
Bert makes his rounds every half an hour.

01:18:07.093 --> 01:18:08.884
You be the lookout.

01:18:55.390 --> 01:18:56.431
Where were you?

01:18:56.432 --> 01:18:57.399
- I didn't see it.

01:18:57.400 --> 01:18:58.856
- Get back to your post.

01:18:58.857 --> 01:18:59.896
- No, let me help.

01:18:59.897 --> 01:19:02.067
The snow's too thick for looking out.

01:19:02.068 --> 01:19:06.193
- If you don't get back to
your post we're going home.

01:19:29.674 --> 01:19:31.007
' Hey, Steve!

01:19:31.008 --> 01:19:31.804
UP here!

01:19:35.346 --> 01:19:36.847
- What are you doing?

01:19:36.848 --> 01:19:38.765
What the heck are you doing?

01:19:38.766 --> 01:19:42.227
- Prying the roof off
so Prancer can jump out.

01:19:42.228 --> 01:19:45.397
- Too high for you and
it's too high for him.

01:19:45.398 --> 01:19:47.107
- He's Prancer, Steve.

01:19:47.108 --> 01:19:49.657
Maybe we'll get to see him fly.

01:19:57.160 --> 01:19:58.036
- Get down!

01:19:59.537 --> 01:20:00.663
- No.

01:20:14.343 --> 01:20:15.720
Come on, Prancer.

01:20:16.971 --> 01:20:17.767
Come on.

01:20:19.348 --> 01:20:20.393
You're all better now.

01:20:20.394 --> 01:20:22.189
There's nothing holding you back.

01:20:22.190 --> 01:20:24.060
Prancer, come on.

01:20:24.061 --> 01:20:25.153
We don't have much time.

01:20:25.154 --> 01:20:27.439
It's quarter till 12.

01:20:28.816 --> 01:20:30.193
Prancer, come on!

01:20:32.236 --> 01:20:33.487
Look, Steve.

01:20:33.488 --> 01:20:36.037
He's gonna fly, he's gonna fly.

01:20:37.575 --> 01:20:38.542
Steve, look!

01:20:53.090 --> 01:20:54.382
- It's Bert.

01:20:54.383 --> 01:20:55.305
Stay put.

01:20:55.306 --> 01:20:58.521
Maybe he won't see you in all the snow.

01:21:48.145 --> 01:21:50.021
- Hey, Prancer.

01:21:50.022 --> 01:21:51.982
How you doing tonight, huh?

01:21:51.983 --> 01:21:54.077
Nice weather we're having here, huh?

01:21:57.238 --> 01:21:58.822
- How about that?

01:21:58.823 --> 01:21:59.619
Yeah.

01:22:00.825 --> 01:22:02.450
Oh, boy'

01:22:02.451 --> 01:22:04.786
Well, we'll see you on our next run

01:22:04.787 --> 01:22:07.916
and I'll bring you something
real good to eat, too, okay?

01:22:07.917 --> 01:22:09.082
Okay.

01:22:09.083 --> 01:22:10.209
See you later.

01:22:30.730 --> 01:22:31.652
- Stay put!

01:22:31.653 --> 01:22:32.773
I'm coming up!

01:22:47.663 --> 01:22:48.628
Jessie!

01:22:49.464 --> 01:22:50.253
Jessie!

01:22:59.508 --> 01:23:00.555
Bert!

01:23:01.385 --> 01:23:02.307
Bert, wait!

01:23:02.308 --> 01:23:03.805
Bert!

01:23:04.639 --> 01:23:06.556
Wait, Bert, stop!

01:23:06.557 --> 01:23:08.350
Bert, my sister's hurt!

01:23:08.351 --> 01:23:09.809
Wait!

01:23:09.810 --> 01:23:11.061
Bert!

01:23:11.062 --> 01:23:11.904
Come back!

01:23:13.147 --> 01:23:14.272
She's hurt!

01:23:14.273 --> 01:23:15.069
Wait!

01:23:15.983 --> 01:23:17.484
Come back, Bert!

01:24:40.985 --> 01:24:41.827
Are you sure?

01:24:41.828 --> 01:24:45.164
I think maybe she came home
from the hospital too soon.

01:24:45.165 --> 01:24:48.116
I know the X-Rays turned out alright.

01:24:48.117 --> 01:24:50.702
She's still not feeling well.

01:24:50.703 --> 01:24:52.205
Things are blurry when she looks at 'em.

01:24:52.206 --> 01:24:54.080
She doesn't want to get out of bed.

01:24:54.081 --> 01:24:56.675
She doesn't want to play
her Christmas records.

01:24:56.676 --> 01:24:58.752
Oh, no, you don't understand.

01:24:58.753 --> 01:25:03.006
My daughter plays
Christmas records all year.

01:25:03.007 --> 01:25:03.883
Yeah, okay.

01:25:05.718 --> 01:25:06.514
I will.

01:25:14.435 --> 01:25:17.020
- How are you feeling, honey?

01:25:17.021 --> 01:25:20.565
Things still look a little funny to you?

01:25:20.566 --> 01:25:21.362
- Sort of.

01:25:32.119 --> 01:25:33.620
- Tomorrow when your uncle and I come over

01:25:33.621 --> 01:25:34.964
for Christmas dinner,

01:25:34.965 --> 01:25:38.917
we'll all get bundled up and
we'll go and see Prancer.

01:25:38.918 --> 01:25:42.218
- I don't want to see that deer anymore.

01:25:44.131 --> 01:25:46.302
- What on earth are you talking about?

01:25:46.303 --> 01:25:47.392
- Everyone was right.

01:25:47.393 --> 01:25:50.970
Don't know why it took
me so long to listen.

01:25:50.971 --> 01:25:53.515
- I don't understand, Jessie.

01:25:53.516 --> 01:25:56.893
- It's just a deer, Aunt Sarah.

01:25:56.894 --> 01:25:59.022
- What would make you say such a thing?

01:25:59.023 --> 01:26:01.523
After all that you've done for him,

01:26:01.524 --> 01:26:04.317
after what he did for you last night?

01:26:04.318 --> 01:26:08.448
Why, I bet Santa's coming
to get him tonight.

01:26:10.825 --> 01:26:12.742
- You don't have to pretend.

01:26:12.743 --> 01:26:13.710
Dad's right.

01:26:13.711 --> 01:26:15.830
I'm almost nine years old.

01:26:18.124 --> 01:26:20.502
It's time I grew up a little.

01:26:45.317 --> 01:26:47.902
- Hey, John, how are you?

01:26:47.903 --> 01:26:49.120
What you doing down here?

01:26:49.121 --> 01:26:51.739
- I was just checking on the reindeer.

01:26:51.740 --> 01:26:52.866
- You ought to go up to your house

01:26:52.867 --> 01:26:54.289
'cause there's gonna be a party there.

01:26:54.290 --> 01:26:55.502
- Uh.

01:26:56.453 --> 01:26:57.745
- Dumb.

01:26:57.746 --> 01:27:00.540
It was supposed to be a surprise party.

01:27:00.541 --> 01:27:01.383
- A what?

01:27:01.384 --> 01:27:05.505
- Just between you and I,
it's a party for Jessie.

01:27:06.505 --> 01:27:09.007
So, we'll see you out there, okay?

01:27:09.008 --> 01:27:09.848
- Well, yeah.

01:27:09.849 --> 01:27:10.684
Sure I'll be there.

01:27:10.685 --> 01:27:11.801
- Okay.

01:27:11.802 --> 01:27:12.598
- Yeah.

