01:28:59.118 --> 01:29:00.335
- That's okay, daddy.

01:29:00.336 --> 01:29:01.544
- No, it isn't.

01:29:04.957 --> 01:29:05.753
It isn't.

01:29:08.669 --> 01:29:10.216
I've been thinking.

01:29:14.425 --> 01:29:18.555
Maybe we could do some of
the things we used to do,

01:29:22.182 --> 01:29:23.559
you know, before?

01:29:25.602 --> 01:29:27.320
On other Christmases.

01:29:34.486 --> 01:29:36.534
You know that old sleigh?

01:29:37.489 --> 01:29:41.619
Remember the rides we used to
take in it every Christmas?

01:29:42.911 --> 01:29:45.538
Well, maybe we could
hook it up to old Ralph

01:29:45.539 --> 01:29:47.257
and do that tomorrow.

01:29:49.335 --> 01:29:51.212
- I'd like that, daddy.

01:30:00.387 --> 01:30:02.936
- I found this out in the shed.

01:30:18.697 --> 01:30:19.537
What?

01:30:19.538 --> 01:30:20.371
- Read it.

01:30:20.372 --> 01:30:21.208
Just this part.

01:30:21.209 --> 01:30:22.747
That's my favorite.

01:30:34.338 --> 01:30:37.340
- You tear apart the baby's rattle,

01:30:37.341 --> 01:30:40.641
and you see what makes the noise inside.

01:30:41.762 --> 01:30:45.598
But there is a veil
covering the unseen world,

01:30:45.599 --> 01:30:49.320
which not the strongest
man could tear apart.

01:30:50.229 --> 01:30:51.105
Only faith,

01:30:52.689 --> 01:30:53.485
poetry,

01:30:54.525 --> 01:30:55.902
love, and romance

01:30:57.653 --> 01:31:00.696
can push aside that curtain

01:31:00.697 --> 01:31:04.076
and view the beauty and the glory beyond.

01:31:09.289 --> 01:31:10.506
Is it all real?

01:31:13.335 --> 01:31:15.670
Virginia, in all this world,

01:31:15.671 --> 01:31:18.891
there is nothing else real and abiding.

01:31:20.384 --> 01:31:21.601
No Santa Claus?

01:31:23.095 --> 01:31:24.642
Thank God he lives,

01:31:26.098 --> 01:31:27.475
and lives forever

01:31:29.059 --> 01:31:31.394
1,000 years from now,

01:31:31.395 --> 01:31:33.944
10 times 10,000 years from now.

01:31:35.107 --> 01:31:39.237
He will continue to make
glad the heart of childhood.

01:31:40.654 --> 01:31:43.656
- I didn't really wanna run away.

01:31:43.657 --> 01:31:45.330
I just, I just wanted

01:31:48.328 --> 01:31:50.288
you to find me

01:31:50.289 --> 01:31:52.915
and bring me back here

01:31:52.916 --> 01:31:56.752
and tell me things were going to be okay,

01:31:56.753 --> 01:31:59.255
like they used to be.

01:31:59.256 --> 01:32:00.303
- Oh, Jessie.

01:32:02.718 --> 01:32:06.429
I can't tell you everything's
going to be all right.

01:32:06.430 --> 01:32:08.264
I wish I could.

01:32:08.265 --> 01:32:12.393
But I know things are always
going to be hard around here.

01:32:12.394 --> 01:32:16.397
Could even be we'll
lose this farm someday.

01:32:16.398 --> 01:32:18.025
But I can bear that.

01:32:19.943 --> 01:32:21.820
What I can't bear is…

01:32:28.869 --> 01:32:31.338
when you were gone last night,

01:32:32.998 --> 01:32:34.591
I saw what it would be like around here

01:32:34.592 --> 01:32:36.460
not to have you around.

01:32:40.172 --> 01:32:42.423
I love you, Jessie.

01:32:42.424 --> 01:32:43.674
- I'm sorry.

01:32:43.675 --> 01:32:45.052
I'm sorry, daddy.

01:32:46.261 --> 01:32:47.057
I'm sorry.

01:32:50.807 --> 01:32:52.684
I love you, too, daddy.

01:32:54.228 --> 01:32:55.445
- I know, baby.

01:32:56.730 --> 01:32:57.570
It's okay.

01:32:57.571 --> 01:32:58.360
Don't cry.

01:32:59.483 --> 01:33:00.735
You're home, honey.

01:33:00.736 --> 01:33:03.613
And that's where you're gonna stay.

01:33:06.865 --> 01:33:09.744
I got something I want to show you.

01:33:17.709 --> 01:33:19.674
- How'd you get him?

01:33:19.675 --> 01:33:22.842
- Tracked Herb down and
gave him his money back.

01:33:22.843 --> 01:33:26.514
I think we still got time to
get him out to Antler Ridge.

01:33:26.515 --> 01:33:29.220
Santa hasn't been to Three Oaks yet.

01:33:29.221 --> 01:33:30.721
- You don't have to.

01:33:30.722 --> 01:33:33.015
I know he's really not Prancer.

01:33:33.016 --> 01:33:34.313
- You're gonna have a lot of trouble

01:33:34.314 --> 01:33:38.439
convincing all those
people downstairs of that.

01:33:40.566 --> 01:33:42.280
Move out of the way, everybody.

01:33:42.281 --> 01:33:45.361
We got a reindeer to get to
Antler Ridge by midnight.

01:33:45.362 --> 01:33:47.078
- I don't think this is
such a good idea, John.

01:33:47.079 --> 01:33:48.790
The doctor said that she
could get out of bed,

01:33:48.791 --> 01:33:51.078
but I don't think this
is what he had in mind.

01:33:51.079 --> 01:33:52.618
She still needs her rest.

01:33:52.619 --> 01:33:53.791
- I know what she needs, Sarah,

01:33:53.792 --> 01:33:56.336
and from now on she's gonna
be getting more of it.

01:34:10.554 --> 01:34:11.350
- Bye!

01:34:13.890 --> 01:34:15.187
- Bye, reindeer!

01:34:17.019 --> 01:34:19.898
- Merry Christmas, Prancer!

01:35:20.791 --> 01:35:24.001
- I wish I could keep
you for just my own pet.

01:35:25.087 --> 01:35:28.339
I'll always remember you, Prancer.

01:35:28.340 --> 01:35:29.216
I love you.

01:35:39.935 --> 01:35:42.563
Thanks, Prancer, for everything.

01:36:28.400 --> 01:36:29.526
- Look.

01:36:36.283 --> 01:36:39.201
- Where did he go?

01:36:39.202 --> 01:36:40.578
- I don't know.

01:36:40.579 --> 01:36:42.206
He just disappeared.

01:36:46.001 --> 01:36:48.880
- He couldn't have jumped and live.

01:36:50.255 --> 01:36:51.552
- Maybe he flew.

01:36:52.632 --> 01:36:56.762
This would be a good place
for Santa to come and get him.

01:37:00.724 --> 01:37:02.271
- The moon is full.

01:37:03.310 --> 01:37:05.438
- And it is Christmas Eve.

01:37:09.149 --> 01:37:09.945
Listen.

01:37:12.486 --> 01:37:14.784
Maybe you'll hear his bells.

01:37:30.545 --> 01:37:31.671
- I hear them.

01:37:33.256 --> 01:37:35.382
I hear them, daddy, I do.

